  "description": "Rule 90's Sierpinski triangle at glacial tempo. Drift pitch mode (pitchMode=1) lets the phase accumulator free-run — notes lose their MIDI-locked pitch and become atmospheric tones that drift against each other in 8-voice polymode. LFO at 0.03 Hz (ultra-slow) morphs projection width over minutes. Very high projection (0.82) means many cells contribute — maximum warmth, maximum diffusion. Hold several notes and let the grid breathe for two minutes. Something will emerge.",
